Ahead of 2021, governorship election, All Progressive Congress APC, Anambra State Chapter is expected to receive over 200,000 supporters from All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA) and People’s Democratic Party (PDP) before the end of January, 2020. The state chairman of the party, Chief Basil Ejidike, stated this Thursday in Awka Anambra state capital. According to him, with the unity the party is currently enjoying with the state leaderships many people are likely to join the party ahead of 2021 governorship election in the state. He said the coming together of likes of Dr. Chris Ngige, Chief George Mogahalu, Chief Johnbosco Onunkwo, Hon. Tony Nwoye, among others, APC in the state is better repositioned to take the leadership in the state comes 2021. “With the contributions of our leaders to the development of the Anambra state, the party is expected to receive about 200,000 supporters from APGA and PDP before the end of January, 2020” he said Anambra 2021:  Start your political activities now, PDP chair tells aspirants APGA’s crisis rages ahead of Anambra guber Confab is all about dividing Nigerians for 2015 - Buba Galadima